            "publication": {
                "license": "ORC",
                "remaster": true,
                "title": "Pathfinder Society Scenario #6-00: Salt of the Ocean"
            },
            "reset": "",
            "routine": "<p><span class=\"action-glyph\">2</span> The demon launch uses its actions on one of the following options (GM’s choice). It loses one action from its routine if a PC succeeds at an attempt to Disable it or it reaches its Broken Threshold.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Broadside Blast</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">a</span> The demon launch makes a Chthonian cannon Strike.</p></li><li><p><strong>Demonic List</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">d</span> <strong>Effect</strong> The ship tosses and turns. Each creature in the hazard’s area must make a @Check[type:reflex|dc:22|showdc:gm]{Reflex save}. On a failure, it is knocked @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Prone]; on a critical failure it also takes @Damage[4d8[bludgeoning]] damage.</p></li><li><p><strong>Heads Will Roll</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">a</span> It makes a bowsprit Strike.</p></li><li><p><strong>Sea Chantey</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">a</span> (auditory) All fiends within 60 feet gain a +1 status bonus to attack rolls, damage rolls, and saves against fear effects; all non-fiends within 60 feet must succeed at a @Check[type:will|dc:22|showdc:gm]{Will save} or become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened]{Frightened 1} (frightened 2 on a critical failure).</p></li></ul>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.campaign-effects.Item.Effect: Sea Chantey]</p>"
